---
const shots = [
  {
    src: '/screenshots/06-remember.png',
    alt: 'An AI client saving a new memory into Graphnosis',
    caption: 'remember — your AI saves a new memory; Graphnosis asks which engram before anything is written.',
    w: 1600,
    h: 1052,
  },
  {
    src: '/screenshots/07-recall.png',
    alt: 'An AI client recalling a memory from Graphnosis',
    caption: 'recall — later, any AI client pulls it straight from your encrypted graph and answers grounded in it.',
    w: 1600,
    h: 1040,
  },
];
---

<section id="ai-demo" class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-[#1c1c27]">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <span class="block text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-[#67e8f9] mb-4">The recall / remember loop</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-4">Watch your AI use it</h2>
      <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Any MCP-aware AI client can read from and write to your Cortex. Tell it to remember something — Graphnosis asks which engram before it writes — and it's there the next time you ask, in that client or any other.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      {shots.map((s) => (
        <figure>
          <img
            src={s.src}
            alt={s.alt}
            width={s.w}
            height={s.h}
            loading="lazy"
            class="w-full rounded-lg border border-[#2a2a3d]"
          />
          <figcaption class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] text-center mt-3">{s.caption}</figcaption>
        </figure>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="text-xs text-[#555570] text-center mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
      Claude is shown here to demonstrate the integration. Graphnosis is an independent product — not affiliated with, or endorsed by, Anthropic.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
